      "content": "Those intense, physical sensations like a static charge or a metallic taste are described medically as synesthesia or severe hypnagogic hallucinations and can sometimes indicate neurological conditions requiring professional evaluation. While rare cases of genuine precognitive phenomena exist in folklore, feeling something that specific without knowing the cause often points to an underlying physiological issue rather than coincidence. Given how vivid and unsettling these experiences are, consulting a doctor or therapist is the safest and most important next step to understand what is happening to your brain.",
